Why was data driven decision making (3DM) useful in this business case?

Dominoâs had to perform better then itâs competitors to become the worldâs leading pizza chain. Their goal was to outperform itâs direct competitors. By trying to do so they used analytics and transformed themselves from a pizza company into a technology company (Van Belleghem, 2019; Splunk, 2019).

How did the organization apply 3DM?

Dominoâs transformed itâs company from an operations-focused business to a customer focused business says Stephen Kennedy, Director Digital Marketing & Media at Dominoâs (Pure Storage, 2020). Using data and deriving decisions from them made it possible to change the customer experience for the better. This is possibly done by extracting, preparing and blending the data. Then a descriptive analysis is performed from where a Diagnostic analysis showed the preference of the customers. This process is visualized in the figure below.

Figure 1. A process model for data-driven decision making taken from Lu, Cairns, and Smith (2020)

One of the improvements stemming from the analytics is the possibility to tap one button to order the same pizza(âs) a customer ordered last time. Either be it on a phone, pc or actual physical button (Van Belleghem, 2019). Other improvements are the introduction of the pizza tracker and later the gps tracker. The pizza tracker shows the progress of the making, baking and possible delivery of an order (Dominoâs New Zealand, 2014; Dominoâs Pizza Netherlands, n.d.). The gps tracker is a later addition to the customers ability to track. It shows precisely where the delivery driver is at the moment and how long it will take them to get to the adress (Dominoâs Pizza Netherlands, n.d.). Using that information customers can prepare for receiving the pizzaâs and paying for them.

The accessibility to real-time data also meant the possibility for a quick turnaround when need be. Per example marketing campaigns: when these donât perform as intended they can be altered to better fit the goal expected to be reached says Jason McMann, Director eCommerce Development Operationâs at Dominoâs (Tealium, 2019).

What can the organization do with 3DM that they couldnât do before?

Develop better customer experiences by using the insights the analytics brought up. This way they could decide on what features to focus on or even see correlations that are not easily seen without analyzing the data. Based on the new findings action can be taken increasing the performance of the company (Tealium, 2019).
